SIMPLE: outbreak
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: outbreak
<hw>out"break`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
bursting forth; eruption; insurrection; mutiny; revolt.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Mobs and <xex>outbreaks</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J. H.
Newman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The flash and <qex>outbreak</qex> of a fiery mind.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sudden beginning of a violent event; <as>as, the
<ex>outbreak</ex> of hostilities between ethnic groups</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A sudden occurrence or manifestation; -- usually of
disease or emotion, in one person or a group; <as>as, an
<ex>outbreak</ex> of measles among the students; he had an
<ex>outbreak</ex> of shingles; an <ex>outbreak</ex> of nervousness in
the mob</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outbreaking</ent>⟦br⟧
